                    "@type": "Question",
                    "name": "How do index funds work?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "Index funds are a special type of financial vehicle that pools money from investors and invests it in securities such as stocks or bonds. An index fund aims to track the returns of a designated stock market index. A market index is a hypothetical portfolio of securities that represents a segment of the market. For example, the S&amp;amp;P 500 index represents 500 of the largest U.S. companies.",
                        "author": {
                            "@type": "Organization",
                            "name": "The Motley Fool"
