<section class="block-faq">
<div class="my-48 wagtail-block">
<h2>Index Fund FAQs</h2>
<div class="qna">
<div class="flex items-center justify-between py-24 border-b border-gray-400 qna-header hub-faq">
<h3 data-block-key="uqupe">How do index funds work?</h3>
<svg class="collapsed-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-down</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M151.5 347.8L3.5 201c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l19.8-19.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0L160 282.7l119.7-118.5c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0l19.8 19.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-148 146.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0z"></path>
</svg>
<svg class="expanded-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-up</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M168.5 164.2l148 146.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-19.8 19.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L160 229.3 40.3 347.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L3.5 328c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l148-146.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0z"></path>
</svg>
</div>
<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="v25cf">Index funds are a special type of financial vehicle that pools money from investors and invests it in securities such as stocks or bonds. An <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/how-to-invest/index-funds/how-index-funds-work/">index fund</a> aims to track the returns of a designated <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/indexes/">stock market index</a>. A market index is a hypothetical portfolio of securities that represents a segment of the market. For example, the <b>S&amp;P 500 index</b> represents 500 of the largest U.S. companies.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="qna">
<div class="flex items-center justify-between py-24 border-b border-gray-400 qna-header hub-faq">
<h3 data-block-key="usohg">What is the average index fund return?</h3>
<svg class="collapsed-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-down</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M151.5 347.8L3.5 201c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l19.8-19.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0L160 282.7l119.7-118.5c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0l19.8 19.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-148 146.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0z"></path>
</svg>
<svg class="expanded-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-up</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M168.5 164.2l148 146.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-19.8 19.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L160 229.3 40.3 347.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L3.5 328c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l148-146.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0z"></path>
</svg>
</div>
<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="pnh2j">The <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/how-to-invest/index-funds/average-return/">average annual return</a> for the S&amp;P 500 is close to 10% over the long term. The performance of the S&amp;P 500 index is better in some years than it is in others, though.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="qna">
 <div class="flex items-center justify-between py-24 border-b border-gray-400 qna-header hub-faq">
<h3 data-block-key="fs1k8">What are low cost index funds?</h3>
<svg class="collapsed-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-down</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M151.5 347.8L3.5 201c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l19.8-19.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0L160 282.7l119.7-118.5c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0l19.8 19.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-148 146.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0z"></path>
</svg>
<svg class="expanded-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-up</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M168.5 164.2l148 146.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-19.8 19.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L160 229.3 40.3 347.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L3.5 328c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l148-146.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0z"></path>
</svg>
